ating resource bundle caching**\\n\\nI'm examining how the root bundle exists for tests and dependencies, and it seems like there's potential for ResourceBundle caching across tests. The application test loads APPLICATION_BUNDLE first, followed by jakarta.faces.Messages; if others load the standard with Locale.ROOT first, that could affect the order. JUnit test executions might cause dependencies to cache beforehand. It’s quite nuanced with potential issues related to classpath order, particularly with Gradle. I should consider naming conventions in resources.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing MessageFactory behavior**\\n\\nI’m delving into the MessageFactory at line 135, where it seems that the UISelectOne INVALID causes bundle.getString to throw, leaving the summary null. Then at line 152, it retrieves the Mojarra bundle. If the ResourceBundle parent chain includes a dependency base as a parent, that could complicate things. The test property shouldn’t have this dependency. I think I will need to review all property bundles in Native Image, especially if there are multiple resources with the same name. Also, noting that no tests were run is important.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xsxLrPb9IEWRGkLvYcZLeQnw|fc_03f8cc70316f0e9c016a01f556206c8197bfd54887a132a41d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short && git diff -- tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/MessageFactoryTest.java tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/resources/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/MessageFactoryMessages.properties tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/resources/jakarta/faces/Messages.properties tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/resources/com/sun/faces/resources/Messages.properties", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input