[assistant] Fixed `MessageFactoryTest`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause: `TestFacesContext` eagerly constructed a `UIViewRoot` before `FacesContext.setCurrentInstance(...)` was called. `UIViewRoot` extends `UIComponentBase`, whose constructor can call `FacesContext.getCurrentInstance()`. With no current context, Jakarta Faces falls back through `FactoryFinder`, which expects Mojarra implementation classes like `com.sun.faces.util.Util` that are not present in the API-only artifact.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - Removed eager `UIViewRoot` construction.
[assistant] - `getViewRoot()` now returns `null`, which exercises the `MessageFactory` default-locale path.
[assistant] - Temporarily sets `Locale.ROOT` while each test context is active, then restores the original default locale in `release()`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated file:
[assistant] - `tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/MessageFactoryTest.java`
