[assistant] Updated `MessageFactoryTest` to avoid `UIComponentBase` state-helper access paths that require absent Mojarra implementation class `com.sun.faces.util.Util`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes made:
[assistant] - `TestInput` now overrides:
[assistant]   - `getAttributes()`
[assistant]   - `getClientId(...)`
[assistant]   - `isRequired()`
[assistant]   - `getRequiredMessage()`
[assistant]   - `isValid()`
[assistant]   - `setValid(...)`
[assistant] - `TestSelectOne` now overrides:
[assistant]   - `getAttributes()`
[assistant]   - `getClientId(...)`
[assistant]   - `getConverter()`
[assistant]   - `isValid()`
[assistant]   - `setValid(...)`
[assistant] - Removed calls to `setId(...)`, `setRequired(...)`, and renderer setup from the tests.
[assistant] 
[assistant] This keeps the tests focused on reaching `jakarta.faces.component.MessageFactory` bundle lookup paths while avoiding unrelated Jakarta Faces API scaffolding that delegates to unavailable implementation internals in the API-only artifact.
[assistant-event] text_end
